The paper presents a distributed performance-testing framework that coordinates a pool of machines to test a target service, collects and aggregates performance metrics, and generates performance statistics. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Networking and Internet Architecture, and Software Engineering categories. The paper also mentions testing on two testbeds, Grid3 and PlanetLab, which suggests that it could belong to the Performance category. Finally, the paper focuses on testing job submission services included with Globus Toolkit/spl reg/ 3.2, which suggests that it could belong to the Programming Languages category.
